# xray — example environment file.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored and MUST NEVER be COPYied
# into the Docker image — secrets enter at `docker run` time only.
# See .claude/rules/public-repo.md §2.

# --- Server ---
# Port the Bun process listens on inside the container.
PORT=8080
# Bind address. The validated default (loaded from env.ts) is `127.0.0.1` — safe
# for `bun src/server/main.ts` on a host. Inside Docker (via `compose.yaml`)
# the container's compose file overrides this to `0.0.0.0`; do NOT bake
# `HOST=0.0.0.0` into a shell-level `.env` or you'll expose the
# unauthenticated API to your LAN.
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# Directory holding the SQLite store file (`xray.db`). In Docker this is the
# mounted volume; locally with `bun src/server/main.ts` set it to `./data`.
XRAY_DATA_DIR=/data
# Optional override for the audio root. Defaults to `$XRAY_DATA_DIR/audio`.
# Per-turn and full-replay audio files live here, indexed by replay id.
# XRAY_AUDIO_ROOT=/data/audio

# --- Providers (server-side) ---
# Required for the analyze chain. Whisper transcribes each VAD-detected
# turn; the judge LLM evaluates `Judge.text_match` assertions. The server
# boots cleanly without these, but the first `/analyze` call hits a stage
# that needs them and stamps `failure_reason='missing_credential'` until
# they're set. Pass at runtime; never bake into the image.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Override the judge model snapshot. Defaults to `gpt-4o-2024-08-06` (a
# pinned snapshot, not a floating alias — verdict drift between days
# breaks tests silently). Set to a newer snapshot when you've verified
# your test bench against it.
# XRAY_JUDGE_MODEL=gpt-4o-2024-08-06

# --- Dev compose ---
# Run dev containers as the host user so files written into the bind-mounted
# repo (./:/app) are owned by you, not root. Without these, a compromised dev
# dependency could write to .git/hooks, package.json, etc. with root perms.
#   export UID GID                 # bash/zsh
UID=1000
GID=1000

# Docker Compose project name. Pinned here so the dev container's name and
# named volumes stay deterministic regardless of how the parent directory is
# named or whether it resolves through a symlink. scripts/new-worktree.sh
# overrides this per worktree by appending its own value at the tail of the
# new worktree's .env (last assignment wins per dotenv semantics).
COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=xray

# Host-side port that compose.dev.yaml maps to the container's :8080. Override
# this per worktree to run multiple dev stacks in parallel; scripts/new-worktree.sh
# picks the lowest free port at or above 8081 automatically. A typo here
# (non-numeric, empty string) produces a confusing Docker error at `up` time
# rather than a `.env`-level validation, so be deliberate when editing.
# HOST_PORT=8080

# Host-side port that compose.dev.yaml maps to the docs (VitePress) dev server's
# :5173. Browse the live docs at http://localhost:${DOCS_PORT}/xray/. Override
# per worktree to run parallel docs servers alongside HOST_PORT.
# DOCS_PORT=5173
